Q. What does style-loader and css-loader do?

Ans: css-loader is the npm module that would help webpack to collect CSS from all the css files referenced in your application 
and put it into a string. And then style-loader would take the output string generated by the above css-loader and 
put it inside the <style> tags in the index.

Q. What does scss-loader do?

Ans: it compiles all the scss/sass into css files